data.title: It's more fun in Plaridel!
data.text:
One of the town’s major attractions is the Simborio Chapel. One of the oldest existing structure from the Spanish era, believed to have been constructed in the 1800s, is said to have been greatly unique from other similar structures because of its remarkably rather low height or elevation. Plaridel, Bulacan, Jan. 17, 2001 – A fiesta for horse lovers is the popular two-day celebration called “Pintakasi ng mga Caballero” held before New Year’s Eve in Plaridel, Bulacan. Filipinos are well-known to be courageous and freedom lovers. The people of Plaridel are no exception. The marker commemorates the historic Battle of Quingua (Plaridel at present) where the Filipinos triumphed over the American forces in their fight for freedom.
